				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">air pet (not planning on using epic) 
<br />
boV 
<br />
velocity (will trade out once pet is buffed) 
<br />
anull 
<br />
mala 
<br />
nukes? 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'd trade the air pet for the 65 earth pet if you have it. If you don't, I'd stick to the epic believe it or not. The epic's procs will land FAR more than the 61 air pet's stun and the damage differential with the PVP nerf isn't very significant.
<br />

<br />
Definitely keep velocity up.
<br />

<br />
Definitely keep Mala up.
<br />

<br />
If you can swap out BO5 after buff for a second nuke that'd be great.
<br />

<br />
I find that black steel is nearly useless on people who have VT or EP gear. If your opponents are geared to this level, stick to your fire nukes as their FR is probably lower than their MR. Sun Vortex's cast time is awful, but it has the biggest bang for the mana costs. Similarly bad cast times can be had with FOT, however crits with FOT are killler and the range, if you can keep it, can buy you the time you need to get a cast off, especially in mass pvp where people are likely to be distracted by others.
<br />

<br />
Annul is something I'd also keep in my lineup if I had a choice though it tends to be crushed by people who have instaclicks (like AON's, gobby earings or Ring 8/9/10s).<br />_________________<br /><span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">Sage Svenuce Summonstuff</span></span>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Vallon Zek
<br />
Officer of <a href="http://zep.blogspot.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zephyros</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
