			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Don't plan on keeping your buffs long, junk buff yourself first, levy, see invis etc.  Get focus, get virtue, get kei.. let them be last.
<br />

<br />
Keep dispell up, use your epic pet, and keep your air pet ready as well as a spare epic rod on your bag.  Use HoE if you have them on all the casters/healers.  Get a root web from cc if you can to keep others pets off of you [like shaman dogs..].
<br />

<br />
You're not a wizard-so fast nukes aren't going to allow you to win
<br />
You're not a cleric-you can't heal yourself
<br />
You do hands down have the best pet in the game though.  Have him take out the most wicked caster first.  Don't send him after a pet or a mele.  Rangers bows will give you more trouble than a straight mele though.  You can always run around the arena buying time.  Rains take long to cast, use FoT/mala if you can.  You also have no way to blind them.. keep an insta clicky up like the invis rods we summon etc.
<br />

<br />
Sounds like a lot of work for 1 pvp battle right? LOL..it is.  You have to size up every other class.  If there is another mage in the battle, take the pet out first of course.  Necro pets are brutal, mb'ing wizards are brutal.  Always go for the casters first, then the mele.
<br />

<br />
Good Luck <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Phenomena Alexicacon</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
